A vintage 1950s travel poster style illustration of a weary traveler with a suitcase standing at an airport terminal, gazing through massive floor-to-ceiling windows at a dramatic sunrise-sunset sky split in half—golden dawn on one side, deep purple twilight on the other. Multiple analog clocks float in the sky showing different times, their hands spinning in opposite directions. The traveler's shadow stretches impossibly long across the polished floor, fragmenting into multiple overlapping silhouettes suggesting temporal disorientation. Warm amber and cool indigo color palette with retro halftone textures and worn paper grain effects.
